  <english_manuscript>Todbj&#xE6;rg church was supposed to have stood on Krajbj&#xE6;rg field. They hitched two oxen together and they walked over to Todbj&#xE6;rg and lay down. They couldn't get anything to stay up, it got torn down during the night, and so they drove the oxen.</english_manuscript>
  <danish_publication>Todbj&#xE6;rg Kirke skulde have ligget paa Krajbj&#xE6;rg Mark; men de kunde ingen Ting faa til at staa, for det blev revet ned om Natten. Saa koblede de to Stude sammen og drev dem af Sted. De gik til Todbj&#xE6;rg og lagde dem.</danish_publication>
  <english_publication>Todbj&#xE6;rg church was supposed to have stood on Krajbj&#xE6;rg field; but they couldn&#x2019;t get anything to stay up, because it was torn down at night. Then they hitched two steers together and drove them off. They went to Todbj&#xE6;rg and lay down.</english_publication>
